1
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:22,500
We dropped by Matnog (Town)
to buy these!

2
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,867
That's the important appointment
you went to?

3
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,033
Celeste, no.

4
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:27,233
Your Auntie Adora and I came
from the hospital.

5
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:28,667
I had her checked
by the doctor.

6
00:00:28,733 --> 00:00:33,033
So, you prioritized her
instead of visiting my mother?

7
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,767
She's always your priority.

8
00:00:34,867 --> 00:00:38,033
You just allow Manay
to answer you back that way.

9
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,667
I don't understand either.

10
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,433
Sometimes I also get tired.

11
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,667
You are tired?

12
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:44,400
It's me who's tired!

13
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:48,267
I've been hurting
for almost half of my life...

14
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,967
because of all of you!

15
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,400
You know how important
this day to me is.

16
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:55,500
I was only asking for one day
and you can't give it.

17
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:57,200
For me...

18
00:00:57,267 --> 00:01:00,433
for your wife
who died because of you!

19
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,033
Do you think I'm happy?

20
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,233
Do you think I'm happy
with all of these?

21
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,433
No, I'm not!

22
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,833
I'm empty!

23
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:11,033
I'm broken...

24
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:13,000
because I don't have a mother.

25
00:01:13,067 --> 00:01:14,767
The day is not yet over.

26
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:18,167
We can still visit
your mother Lucinda now.

27
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,633
The four of us will go there
together.

28
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,767
- Let's leave right now.
- It's too late.

29
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:22,400
- Let's go.
- No, it's too late.

30
00:01:22,467 --> 00:01:25,700
It's okay. It's fine.

31
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:26,467
And you know, honestly,
thank you
because of what I saw today.

32
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:28,767
You did me a favor.

33
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,433
You only proved that...

34
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,333
I can never depend on you
anymore.

35
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:39,533
So, if you expect me to glorify
your father's name...

36
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,433
he's all yours.

37
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:46,667
For Celeste,
I'm a worthless person...

38
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,733
but I will endure it.

39
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:53,967
But, Patricio, how long
will I fight my decision

40
00:01:54,033 --> 00:01:56,967
to love you?

41
00:01:57,033 --> 00:02:00,700
Someday,
everything will be fixed.

42
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:02,167
Father, Celeste is old enough.

43
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:03,800
She knows what she's doing.

44
00:02:03,867 --> 00:02:06,100
I always hurt Celeste.

45
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:09,000
I have a bad feeling that
she will not come home.

46
00:02:09,067 --> 00:02:13,133
I hope the day won't end
without us making amends.

47
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,167
Hello, Sir?

48
00:02:14,267 --> 00:02:15,367
Mikoy...

49
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:17,433
we need your help.

50
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,333
Celeste is missing.

51
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,867
What?

52
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:44,533
Mother, Father...

53
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:47,233
I can't contact Celeste.

54
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,500
You still can't reach her?

55
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,333
I can't.

56
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,400
Where is she?

57
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,933
Hey...

58
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,500
it's Mikoy.

59
00:02:58,567 --> 00:02:59,733
Just in time.

60
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,600
- Sir Patricio.
- We can ask help to him.

61
00:03:01,667 --> 00:03:02,600
What happened?

62
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,300
Mikoy...

63
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:07,167
Celeste and I had an argument.

64
00:03:07,233 --> 00:03:08,700
It's a long story.

65
00:03:08,767 --> 00:03:09,667
She's missing.

66
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,067
She suddenly left.

67
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:13,733
I'm worried she might
stay out too late.

68
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,967
Mikoy, you and Celeste
are always together.

69
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:18,133
Maybe you know
where to find her.

70
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:22,733
Hey, wait Celeste!

71
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,900
Celeste, wait!

72
00:03:25,067 --> 00:03:26,567
What is your problem?

73
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:28,033
Why are you crying?

74
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:32,067
I don't want this anymore.

75
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:38,433
I want to go to a far place
where I can't see father.

76
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,333
Why? What happened to you?

77
00:03:41,533 --> 00:03:43,133
- Just let me, Mikoy.
- Celeste, stay here.

78
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,367
Let go of me!

79
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:45,533
Calm down.

80
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,300
I won't stop until you tell me.

81
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:50,467
Calm down.

82
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:53,267
Celeste...

83
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,433
why are you like that?

84
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,367
Mikoy, I don't want this
anymore.

85
00:03:59,167 --> 00:04:00,867
I don't want to go home.

86
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:05,333
I don't want to see
father's family!

87
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,267
I don't want this anymore!

88
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,000
I'm tired.

89
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,867
I know where she is.

90
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:39,967
You already you know?

91
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:42,000
Come on, let's go!

92
00:04:42,067 --> 00:04:43,333
I'll just go alone.

93
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,800
I'll just bring her back to you.

94
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:45,900
Mikoy...

95
00:04:45,967 --> 00:04:46,833
I want to fetch...
- Patricio...
- my daughter.

96
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,733
Patricio just leave it to Mikoy.

97
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,533
The more Celeste might not
come home if she sees you.

98
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:57,267
But, Mikoy...

99
00:04:58,467 --> 00:05:00,800
you should come back
with my daughter.

100
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,100
Promise me that.

101
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,800
I'll take care of it.

102
00:05:05,667 --> 00:05:06,833
I'll go ahead.

103
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:07,667
Bye, Mikoy.

104
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:09,367
You take care.

105
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:13,367
Aw...

106
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:16,467
Oh my god.

107
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,900
Ah...

108
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:21,700
Shocks...

109
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:30,033
Ouch!

110
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:36,733
Shocks...

111
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:03,600
Ouch!

112
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,433
Aw...

113
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:00,700
Celeste.

114
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,100
Mikoy?

115
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:26,067
What?

116
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:29,800
Will you fight with me again?

117
00:08:29,867 --> 00:08:34,733
Do you really have to scheme
that fool is your boyfriend?

118
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,433
Why not just pretend
that he's your cousin?

119
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,167
How can I prove that?

120
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:41,633
What will I say?

121
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:45,167
James...

122
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,333
Basti is from here.

123
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:51,633
So obviously, Sir Ben knows
his whole family.

124
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,600
That's subject
for more questions.

125
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,200
At least, when I tell them

126
00:08:56,267 --> 00:08:57,800
that I'm his girlfriend,
that's it.

127
00:08:57,867 --> 00:08:58,833
They will believe me.

128
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,067
They won't ask anymore!

129
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:01,433
You sound so desperate.

130
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:05,600
I am because we're racing
against the clock, James.

131
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:08,033
We're left behind
in our project.

132
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:10,067
Where else can we look?

133
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,900
Maybe you're just making
our project an excuse.

134
00:09:17,567 --> 00:09:19,367
What's with that Basti
and you agreed

135
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:21,067
with his suggestions?

136
00:09:21,133 --> 00:09:22,767
So, the truth is finally out.

137
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,700
You're jealous, Babe.

138
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:29,567
I know that his intention
is bad.

139
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:32,200
It's just a figment
of your imagination.

140
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,567
You choose...

141
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:38,067
your jealousy...

142
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,600
or do you want us to fail?

143
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:41,933
Of course...

144
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,833
I want to pass.

145
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,100
Then cut the crap!

146
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:46,933
We need to do this.

147
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,800
Okay...

148
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:55,367
I'll agree...

149
00:09:55,433 --> 00:09:57,233
but on one condition.

150
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:59,600
You need to be with me always.

151
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:01,000
You won't be alone
with that guy.

152
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,033
No problem with me at all.

153
00:10:04,533 --> 00:10:06,700
Just don't be a jerk.

154
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,700
You're just mine, Tiffany.

155
00:10:18,067 --> 00:10:19,767
I'm sorry.

156
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:22,933
If only I didn't feel sick,

157
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,767
you could've visited Lucinda
in the cemetery.

158
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:30,600
Love, what happened
is not your fault.

159
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:33,367
You didn't mean
not to feel well.

160
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:37,533
And you really need
to be checked by the doctor.

161
00:10:37,633 --> 00:10:38,867
I don't know.

162
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:42,267
I don't know who to blame.

163
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:45,800
You, me, your daughter.

164
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:48,800
What I know is that it
increased my misdeeds

165
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,633
against her.

166
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,567
Mother, it's not your fault.

167
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:55,533
What if something happens
to you?

168
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:59,133
Who should Father prioritize?

169
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,767
The person who can die

170
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,433
or the person who
is already dead for a long time?

171
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,833
Hey, Sebastian,
watch your mouth.

172
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:08,300
It's not good for you
to say that.

173
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:12,400
Celeste is getting out of hand.

174
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,233
She is narrow-minded.

175
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,667
Shhh...

176
00:11:16,533 --> 00:11:18,467
Stop arguing.

177
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:24,867
Celeste is close-minded...

178
00:11:24,933 --> 00:11:27,600
so let's be more understanding
of her.

179
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:34,667
As for me, I believe that
we can count on Mikoy

180
00:11:34,733 --> 00:11:37,533
that he can bring Celeste back
to us properly.

181
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,167
What happened to you?

182
00:11:56,233 --> 00:11:57,633
I twisted my foot a while ago.

183
00:12:00,167 --> 00:12:01,400
Wait a second.

184
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,300
Wait.

185
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,367
Hey, what are you doing?

186
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,667
Wait.

187
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:31,400
Just relax there.

188
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:35,867
That's gross.

189
00:12:35,933 --> 00:12:38,000
You want me not
to wear this?

190
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,033
- There.
- What are you doing?

191
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:46,067
We'll treat that.

192
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:56,800
Just wait.

193
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:57,733
Give me that.

194
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:58,900
Just a second.

195
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,000
There you go.

196
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,800
Hold this for a while.

197
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,567
Where did you learn that?

198
00:13:12,633 --> 00:13:13,900
I'm a boy scout.

199
00:13:13,967 --> 00:13:15,033
I'm always ready.

200
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:16,867
Just wait.

201
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,067
- Here?
- Yes.

202
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:26,267
My foot is dirty.

203
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:27,967
That's okay.

204
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:31,100
It's okay now.

205
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:08,100
What happened?

206
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:14,967
It's father.

207
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,633
He forgot
Mother's death anniversary.

208
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,033
He prioritized
his second wife again.

209
00:14:22,233 --> 00:14:27,167
And he didn't tell me
that he moved her grave.

210
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,433
It was so annoying.
I looked stupid there.

211
00:14:29,533 --> 00:14:31,867
I'm kept on talking to no one

212
00:14:31,933 --> 00:14:33,500
because mother
is no longer there.

213
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:39,067
I was touched
when he reminded me

214
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:40,933
of Mother's death anniversary

215
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,933
when I had my community service
on the Pili farm.

216
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,233
I thought that...

217
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,800
despite everything that
happened,

218
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:54,233
he left Mother,
he had another family,

219
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:58,233
somehow there's still love left
in his heart

220
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,467
but there's nothing.

221
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:01,867
He didn't think about her...

222
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,233
so what love would he have
in his heart.

223
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:08,600
He prioritized that Adora.

224
00:15:08,667 --> 00:15:12,300
She's all that matters to him.

225
00:15:16,367 --> 00:15:19,100
You shouldn't judge
your father that much.

226
00:15:21,967 --> 00:15:23,400
You should talk.

227
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:27,433
You should also talk
to your Auntie Adora.

228
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:32,400
You know, the fact that he
planned to surprise you...

229
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:33,667
about it...

230
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:37,333
it means that your Mother
Lucinda is still in his heart,

231
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:40,467
right?

232
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:41,700
Don't be too tough.

233
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,833
Come on, let's go home.

234
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:48,767
I will not go home.

235
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,333
I'll stay here.

236
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,600
What?

237
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:54,333
I promised your father
that I will not go back

238
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,467
without you.

239
00:15:58,633 --> 00:16:00,933
Who told you to come here
and fetch me?

240
00:16:02,367 --> 00:16:03,900
You should listen
to what you're saying.

241
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,533
If I didn't arrive,

242
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,033
maybe the more you're limping
right now.

243
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:08,867
It will bleed.

244
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:11,067
There will be bloodshed.

245
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:13,267
Do you want to get married
in a coffin?

246
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:16,067
You're thinking about coffin
right away?

247
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:18,333
You're overreacting.

248
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,567
You will get married soon.

249
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,733
You know the saying that
those who are getting married

250
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,900
are prone to accidents.

251
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:29,133
You know, you can go home
if you want.

252
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:31,333
Here's the thing.

253
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:34,433
Thank you so much by the way
for all you have done for me.

254
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,400
Thank you so much.

255
00:16:35,467 --> 00:16:36,433
Is that okay?

256
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:37,600
You can go home.

257
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:38,800
I'm okay.

258
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:41,467
Anyway, I'm used
to being alone.

259
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,100
I'm used to being
left behind.

260
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:51,900
Okay,
if you want to contemplate,

261
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:53,267
go ahead...

262
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:54,133
but I will not leave you.

263
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,200
I'll stay here.

264
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:56,467
I'll stay with you.

265
00:16:58,033 --> 00:16:59,200
- You will stay here?
- Yes.

266
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,767
Don't mind me.

267
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:01,667
I'm not here.

268
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:03,933
Okay.

269
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,767
Okay.

270
00:17:09,367 --> 00:17:10,600
Don't look at me.

271
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:11,833
You are looking.

272
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,300
Hey, I'm not here.

273
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,400
Got you.

274
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,500
I can't get
through Celeste's phone.

275
00:18:07,133 --> 00:18:08,500
Try calling her later.

276
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,700
Relax.

277
00:18:15,667 --> 00:18:17,267
Can you believe it?

278
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,400
In four months,
Celeste and I will get married.

279
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:23,733
Yet my bride is doing community
service.

280
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,133
Is there any way to speed up
her community service?

281
00:18:28,967 --> 00:18:31,200
I've already talked
to the Mayor.

282
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:33,200
He didn't agree.

283
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,600
I don't want to nag him.

284
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,067
Did you negotiate with him?

285
00:18:40,133 --> 00:18:42,167
Maybe we can just donate.

286
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:45,100
I don't want to ruin
our wedding preparation

287
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:47,167
just because of her community
service.

288
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:50,833
It's not obvious that
you're really in a rush

289
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:51,900
to marry Celeste.

290
00:18:53,133 --> 00:18:57,867
Of course, any man would rush
to marry her.

291
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,267
Yes, Vivian?

292
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:11,233
Tonito, I'll send you some
documents tonight.

293
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:15,533
Read them and let me know
what you think.

294
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:18,433
Okay, Vivian.

295
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,033
Vivian will send some documents.

296
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:28,067
Do you know what this is?

297
00:20:07,233 --> 00:20:08,233
How are you feeling?

298
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,633
It's not too painful anymore.

299
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:15,833
Good thing,
you're okay now somehow.

300
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:19,300
Just wait.

301
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,200
Who will you call?

302
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:27,000
Sir Patricio.

303
00:20:28,367 --> 00:20:29,433
Why?

304
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,000
Don't call them.

305
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,867
They don't care about me.

306
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,900
Celeste, I have to tell him
that we're together.

307
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:40,700
You know, I won't be here
if not for him.

308
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:43,400
I should tell him that
we're together, okay?

309
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,333
Sir?

310
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,133
Mikoy, what happened to you?

311
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,667
Where are you?

312
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,767
How is my daughter?

313
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,333
What happened to her?

314
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,700
Why haven't you come back?

315
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:07,900
Mikoy, I want to talk
to my daughter.

316
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,200
Sir, Celeste, and I
are together now.

317
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:12,133
Don't worry anymore.

318
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:17,433
Mikoy, can we see Celeste
on the phone?

319
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:20,200
Just a second.

320
00:21:20,267 --> 00:21:22,033
Where is she?
She was just beside me.

321
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:26,800
Wait, I'll just switch
the camera.

322
00:21:34,033 --> 00:21:35,433
Did something happen to her?

323
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,633
Why is she limping?

324
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:40,733
She twisted her foot.

325
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,667
She has a slight sprain

326
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:44,300
but I've already applied
first aid.

327
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:48,367
Father, it looks like Celeste
doesn't want to talk.

328
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:53,367
Let's just leave Celeste alone
and let her think things over.

329
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:56,600
Don't worry,
once she's okay tomorrow,

330
00:21:56,667 --> 00:21:57,800
we'll go home right away.

331
00:21:57,867 --> 00:22:00,400
Don't worry anymore,
I'll stay with her.

332
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:03,300
Mikoy, I beg you.

333
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:05,667
Take care of my daughter.

334
00:22:05,733 --> 00:22:09,633
Don't come back
without my daughter.

335
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,967
Yes, I will not leave her.

336
00:22:12,067 --> 00:22:13,167
Okay, Mikoy.

337
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:14,900
Thank you so much.

338
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,100
You take care there, okay?

339
00:22:17,167 --> 00:22:18,533
Yes.

340
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,433
I haven't said thank you.

341
00:22:58,433 --> 00:22:59,867
That's okay. I'm used to it.

342
00:23:01,533 --> 00:23:05,533
You make it sound
like I'm very ungrateful.

343
00:23:06,367 --> 00:23:07,600
You said that not me.

344
00:23:09,233 --> 00:23:11,700
Seriously...

345
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:13,400
thank you so much.

346
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:17,400
You were right.
If you didn't arrive,

347
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:20,367
maybe something bad happened
to me.

348
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:29,267
I'm sorry if sometimes
I'm a troublemaker.

349
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:34,633
Sometimes?

350
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:36,267
It seems always is more
appropriate.

351
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,067
Okay, I'm always
a trouble maker.

352
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,200
Let's change it.

353
00:23:42,967 --> 00:23:44,600
I'm principled.

354
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:49,033
Spoiled brat.

355
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,433
I thought you knew me
but it seems you don't.

356
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,033
You really changed a lot,
Celeste.

357
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:05,400
Manila taught you a lot...

358
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:06,900
and being a troublemaker
is one of them.

359
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:13,733
It's called survival instinct.

360
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:18,967
Sometimes you have to be brave.

361
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,033
You have to be fierce

362
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:26,900
because you have to protect
yourself.

363
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:29,467
I was alone then.

364
00:24:31,333 --> 00:24:35,567
My father has another family.

365
00:24:35,633 --> 00:24:38,267
I have no one to rely on
but myself.

366
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,300
And life was never easy for me.

367
00:24:46,533 --> 00:24:48,533
I've been through a lot.

368
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,800
Unbelievable.

369
00:24:51,567 --> 00:24:52,800
I suffered a lot.

370
00:24:53,667 --> 00:24:56,733
I worked hard a lot to get
to where I am now.

371
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:01,733
But I was broken.

372
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:10,733
Good thing, Tonito came
and he mended me

373
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,867
and made me whole again.

374
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:38,300
I having wronged
Celeste big time.

375
00:25:38,367 --> 00:25:41,767
I pushed her to have
a hardened heart.

376
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:43,833
What are your plans
after the wedding?

377
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:46,567
She's planning to slow down
also with work.

378
00:25:46,633 --> 00:25:48,067
So we could travel

379
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:50,167
and spend time together
and build a family.

380
00:25:50,233 --> 00:25:52,267
How I wish we did that.

381
00:25:58,167 --> 00:26:00,400
What's with you?
What are you doing?

382
00:26:00,467 --> 00:26:01,867
Are you a maniac?

383
00:26:01,933 --> 00:26:04,900
You know that we have the same
goal for your dad, right?

384
00:26:04,967 --> 00:26:07,767
And that is to complete
our family again.

385
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:11,500
The only obstacle to our goal
is none other than Celeste.

386
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,067
Why did you move our meeting?

387
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:14,867
Celeste is in trouble.

388
00:26:14,933 --> 00:26:16,033
I need to go there.

389
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:18,167
And just for that woman,

390
00:26:18,233 --> 00:26:20,867
you will move this
important meeting with me?

391
00:26:20,933 --> 00:26:21,900
Are you okay?

392
00:26:21,967 --> 00:26:28,600
I'm a bit cold.

393
00:26:28,667 --> 00:26:31,200
Come here.

394
00:26:31,267 --> 00:26:32,767
You're cold, right?
